Modernized, PT-BR optimized fork of [sc0ty/subsync](https://github.com/sc0ty/subsync).

## Highlights
- **Vosk speech engine** replaces PocketSphinx — dramatically better PT-BR recognition
- **ASS/SSA subtitle support** — styling and formatting fully preserved, only timing changes
- **Accent-insensitive matching** — handles ação/acao, você/voce correctly
- **FFmpeg 5.x/6.x/7.x** compatible (with 4.x backward compat)
- **Pre-bundled PT-BR model** — works out of the box, no extra downloads needed
- **Installs alongside original subsync** — different app name and GUID

## Fixes in This Release (vs upstream)
| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| #188 | Last subtitle line no longer extends to end of video |
| #182/#97 | Filenames with `{}` braces no longer cause "Invalid output pattern" |
| #191 | CLI mode no longer spawns a visible console window on Windows |
| #160 | Clear error message when sync fails (shows point count + suggestions) |
| #135 | Ctrl+C saves partial result if correlation was achieved |
| #164 | Small offset (<2s) subtitles now sync correctly (lowered minPointsNo) |
| #165 | Default language and view mode settings added |
| #102 | Taskbar progress indicator on Windows |
| #155 | Comprehensive documentation (CLI reference, batch patterns, config guide) |
| — | Float → int casts for wxPython 4.2 strict type checking |
| — | Division-by-zero in Line constructor |
| — | RAII cleanup for audio/subtitle decoders |
| — | SpeechRecognition flush() actually drains final buffer |
| — | cmdargs returns {} on error instead of None |

## Downloads
- **`subsync-ptbr-portable.exe`** — Portable executable (no install needed, PT-BR model bundled)
